<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,457,1662,1688]" box="[189,457,1662,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,1662,1688]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,1662,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,1709,1914]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Male genitalia in 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[389,641,1709,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujisanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[389,641,1709,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Aprionus fujisanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[646,735,1710,1736]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Yukawa, 1967" authorityName="Yukawa" authorityYear="1967" box="[788,1150,1709,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitegminis">
<emphasis box="[788,813,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[819,979,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">longitegminis</emphasis>
Yukawa, 1967
</taxonomicName>
are generally similar, but the latter has a slightly different tegmen and the ninth tergite is shorter (
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C." box="[1078,1395,1745,1771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 333" refId="ref16745" refString="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C. 2009. The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia Dipterologica Supplement 18: 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">
Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 
<date box="[1332,1395,1745,1771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2009">2009</date>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 74A, 76D). The strongly recurved CuA present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[822,992,1781,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujisanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[822,992,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. fujisanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[998,1088,1781,1807]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(↓, 
<figureCitation box="[1132,1222,1780,1807]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) is shared with both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yukawa" authorityYear="1967" box="[248,440,1816,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitegminis">
<emphasis box="[248,440,1816,1843]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. longitegminis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof" authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2009" box="[495,871,1816,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevitegminis">
<emphasis box="[495,520,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[527,686,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">brevitegminis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C." box="[692,871,1816,1842]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 333" refId="ref16745" refString="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C. 2009. The Wood Midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae: Lestremiinae) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Studia Dipterologica Supplement 18: 1 - 333." type="journal article" year="2009">Jaschhof, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but not with other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1963" box="[1283,1399,1816,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1399,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Throughout this group, antennal translucent sensilla tend to branch, but this is most pronounced in 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[219,391,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujisanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[219,391,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. fujisanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[398,488,1888,1914]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(↓, 
<figureCitation box="[534,625,1888,1914]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,403,1953,1980]" box="[189,403,1953,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,403,1953,1980]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,403,1953,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Other characters</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,410,2001,2027]" lastBlockId="5.[189,1399,267,364]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Body size 
<quantity box="[313,406,2001,2027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<potCollectionCode box="[189,252,268,294]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">HEAD</potCollectionCode>
. Eye bridge 2–3 ommatidia long dorsally. A sparse row of 6–7 postocular bristles. Neck of fourth flagellomere as long as node or slightly longer; translucent sensilla usually branched, rarely simply hairshaped (
<figureCitation box="[286,379,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Palpus with 3 segments, first segment swollen, apical segment longest of all.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1122,403,435]" box="[189,1122,403,435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<potCollectionCode box="[189,253,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[189,253,404,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">WING</collectionCodeEnum>
</potCollectionCode>
. ApicR 
<subScript attach="left" box="[343,352,421,435]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">1</subScript>
3.0–3.5 times as long as Rs. CuA reaches wing margin (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1109,403,429]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,998,469,495]" box="[189,998,469,495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<potCollectionCode box="[189,246,469,495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[189,246,469,495]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">LEGS</collectionCodeEnum>
</potCollectionCode>
. Claws sickle-shaped, toothless. Empodia half as long as claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,534,736]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<potCollectionCode box="[189,322,535,561]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">TERMINALIA</potCollectionCode>
. Ninth tergite long, posterior margin almost straight, posterolateral shoulders slightly apparent, anterior margin fully sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[725,823,569,595]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1119,569,595]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): ventrobasal apodeme poorly sclerotized, especially anteriorly; medial extensions of gonocoxal apodemes weakly sclerotized, not interconnected medially. Gonostylus blunt-ended, 1+1 short bristles among dense setulae and microtrichia apically, dorsoapical and ventrobasal portions same size (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1101,675,701]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Tegmen slender, central opening inconspicuous, slit-like (
<figureCitation box="[579,674,710,736]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,533,775,802]" box="[189,533,775,802]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,533,775,802]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,533,775,802]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,822,884]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">This species is known from a small series of specimens collected in early June on Japan’s highest mountain peak, Mount Fuji.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
